{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"flap-meal-boast","description":"`rebar session-logs` silently returns nothing when the limit is passed in the\nspace-separated form (`--limit 30`) instead of the equals form (`--limit=30`).\nThe read-side CLI commands only accept `--opt=value`, while write/composer\ncommands (and even `ready` in the same module) accept the `--opt value` space\nform, so the option-value syntax is inconsistent across the CLI and the repo's\nown docs use the space form (e.g. `claim <id> --assignee <you>`). An agent\nfollowing that convention runs `session-logs --limit N`, gets a 2-line error on\nstderr, and — if stderr is discarded or the output is piped — sees an empty\nresult and wrongly concludes there are no session logs.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. Ensure session logs exist (`rebar session-logs` with no args lists them).\n2. Run `rebar session-logs --limit 5` (space-separated form).\n3. Observe: `Error: unknown option '--limit'` + usage on stderr, exit code 2.\n4. Run `rebar session-logs --limit=5` (equals form) → works, exit 0.\n5. Same split elsewhere: `rebar list --status open` → exit 2; `--status=open` → 0.\n\n## Expected\n- `--limit 30` (space form) is accepted, OR option-value syntax is consistent\n  across all CLI commands and matches the documented `--opt <value>` convention.\n- A flag-parsing error is never mistaken for \"no results\": the symptom that the\n  command \"comes back empty\" should not happen for a mere arg-form mismatch.\n\n## Actual\n- `_cmd_session_logs` (src/rebar/_engine_support/reads_cli.py:236-252) matches\n  only `arg.startswith(\"--limit=\")`; the space form falls to the `else` →\n  `unknown option '--limit'`, exit 2.\n- Inconsistency is intra-file: `_cmd_ready` (reads_cli.py:302-311) accepts BOTH\n  `--epic <id>` and `--epic=<id>`; `claim --assignee <you>` (composer parser,\n  src/rebar/_commands/composer.py:477-480) accepts the space form too.\n\n## Notes\n- Root cause is arg-form parsing, not the session-log store: data is present and\n  the equals form returns it correctly. Severity is low (workaround = use `=`),\n  but it is a recurring agent-facing footgun and a CLI-consistency defect.\n- Fix should address the read-CLI option parser class (session-logs `--limit`,\n  list `--status`, and peers), not just session-logs, so the space form is\n  accepted uniformly. Decide deliberately whether to standardize on accept-both\n  (recommended, matches docs) or to reject space-form everywhere and fix the docs.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `rebar session-logs --limit 30` (space form) returns the same result as\n      `rebar session-logs --limit=30` (no \"unknown option\" error).\n- [ ] Option-value parsing is consistent across the read-CLI commands in\n      `reads_cli.py` (at minimum `session-logs --limit` and `list --status`\n      accept the same form(s) as `ready --epic`).\n- [ ] The chosen convention (accept-both vs equals-only) matches the documented\n      usage in CLAUDE.md / `--help`; whichever is picked, docs and parser agree.\n- [ ] A regression test covers both `--limit 30` and `--limit=30` for\n      `session-logs` (and the analogous `list --status` space/equals forms).","id":"ae39-7afc-c500-497d","parent_id":"","priority":3,"tags":["cli","dx","session-log"],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"CLI: 'session-logs --limit <n>' (space form) rejected as unknown option — read-command flags accept only --opt=value, inconsistent with write commands/docs"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782661496114921001,"uuid":"3d2edb5b-7c05-4d2e-a97c-cecc9b257e41"}